{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, Shneiderman (2020) provided 15 recommendations to bridge the gap between ethical principles of AI and practical steps for ethical governance.",
    "Likewise, there are solution-based papers and papers discussing models, frameworks, and methods for AI developers to enhance their AI ethics implementation.",
    "For example, an article by Vakkuri et al. (2021) presents the AI maturity model for AI software.",
    "In contrast, another article by Vakkuri et al. (2020a) discusses the ECCOLA method for implementing ethically aligned AI systems.",
    "There are also papers presenting the toolkit to address fairness in ML algorithms (Castelnovo et al. 2020) and transparency model to design transparent AI systems (Felzmann et al. 2020)."
  ]
}